  "text": "In this section, some basic definitions and theorems have been expressed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Definition 1. For any real function f (t), t > 0, if there exists a real number p > μ, such that f (t) = t p f 1 (t), where f 1 (t) ∈ C(0, ∞), is said to be in space Cμ, μ ∈ , and it is in the space C n μ if and only if f (n) ∈ Cμ , n ∈ N. ",
